SIMPLE: busted
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: busted
<hw>busted</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Inoperable due to
damage; broken; -- of a machine; <as>as, the coke machine is
<ex>busted</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[informal]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Arrested for committing a crime; -- of a person;
<as>as, the rock star was <ex>busted</ex> for coke
possession.</as>.</def> <mark>[informal]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <mark>[predicate]</mark> <def>same as <er>demoted</er>;
-- said especially of military rank, and often followed by
<ptcl>to</ptcl>; <as>as, he was <ex>busted</ex> to corporal for being
AWOL</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <mark>[predicate]</mark> <def>same as <er>exhausted</er>;
-- of people.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buster</ent>⟦br⟧
